The paper discusses the use of Microsoft Academic for bibliometric analyses, which involves analyzing citation data. This falls under several sub-categories of computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), cybersecurity (cs.CY), databases (cs.DB), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper specifically mentions the retrieval and handling of metadata, which is relevant to digital libraries and databases. The citation analysis also involves information retrieval techniques. The paper does not focus on cybersecurity, but it does mention the importance of accurate metadata, which could be relevant to ensuring the security of academic data. Finally, the use of machine learning algorithms for bibliometric analyses could fall under the category of artificial intelligence.
